windows.question:
Which of the following best describes the anomaly detection results within the time series window spanning steps 995 to 1011?
A) Downward Convex anomaly: Values form a downward convex curve that decreases more sharply than the surrounding trend.
B) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
C) Upward Spike anomaly: There is a sharp upward jump in the measurements.

options.A: Downward Convex anomaly: Values form a downward convex curve that decreases more sharply than the surrounding trend.
options.B: The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
options.C: Upward Spike anomaly: There is a sharp upward jump in the measurements.

windows.answer: A) Downward Convex anomaly: Values form a downward convex curve that decreases more sharply than the surrounding trend.

windows.question:

A) Upward Spike anomaly: There is a sharp upward jump in the measurements.
B) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
C) Sudden Increase anomaly: Values show an unexpected surge relative to adjacent points.

options.A: Upward Spike anomaly: There is a sharp upward jump in the measurements.
options.B: The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
options.C: Sudden Increase anomaly: Values show an unexpected surge relative to adjacent points.

windows.answer: B) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
